When Yakiniku 🇯🇵 (Japanese BBQ) Meets Hanshik 🇰🇷 (Korean cuisine)
@seikoen_torrance has been serving authentic yakiniku for over 40 years… and the flavor tells a story

The original owner, a Korean born and raised in Japan, brought dishes like ssam, kimchi, yukhweh, and yukgaejang to the table — perfectly complementing wagyu, ox tongue, and miso pork belly, all grilled to perfection

Rooted in tradition. Remembered through flavor.

#tasteoframi #라미의맛 #yakiniku #hansik #japanesebbq #koreancuisine #aapifoodiefam #teamhappyfoodies #야끼니꾸 #엘에이맛집 #한식

Japan’s THICKEST tonkatsu has finally landed in the U.S.!
Tonkatsu Marushichi @tonkatsu.07.usa is opening in Torrance, CA on July 7th and will be having a special deal—so don’t miss it! ✨

What makes them special? 
They use premium pork and a low-temp frying method to keep the cutlets extra juicy and tender, which is why the center stays pink
It’s not undercooked, just expertly made

I tried the Katsu Sando and their one-pound Katsudon (takeout only + walk-ins only for this one) and wow… crispy, thick, and full of flavor!

Plus, their tonkatsu sauce is lighter, thinner, and a total game changer

📍Tonkatsu Marushichi
21605 S Western Ave Unit C
Torrance, CA 90501

It’s been a while since I last had @bumsanorganicmilkbar in Koreatown, and it was the perfect time to satisfy my ice cream cravings🍦
So I had to revisit and grabbed two dreamy swirls:

🍫☕️ Chocolate x Korean Coffee in a Cocoa Pebbles cone topped with Fruity Pebbles
🍠 🍓 Taro Milk Tea x Strawberries & Cream in a cup w/ a croffle on the side

What makes Bumsan special?
They serve premium soft serve made with 100% organic, non-GMO, antibiotic-free milk—sourced from Bumsan Farm Co., one of Korea’s leading organic dairy producers 🇰🇷🥛
Sustainable, clean, and creamy in every bite

🅿️: $5 valet

This teriyaki shop has been a neighborhood staple for 25 years!
It’s now run by a Japanese-Korean couple, but still serving up the same flavors longtime regulars love

Heads up: They’ve rebranded to @teriyaki_tei
but the old sign is still up
So don’t get confused when you pull in!

Here’s what we ordered:
🍜 Cold Udon (so refreshing)
🍱 Beef Teriyaki + Chicken Katsu Combo
🍚 Combination Fried Rice
🍵 UCC Matcha Latte (surprisingly good)

Don’t get fooled by the looks—this place is unassuming but the food slaps 🔥
And the most expensive dish is only $13.99! 

Bonus: no parking stress ‘cause they’ve got a huge lot

📍Teriyaki Tei

Los Angeles, CA 90006

North Korean naengmyeon… in LA?! 🇰🇵🍜
This famous Pyongyang naengmyeon spot from Seoul just opened and we had to try it

The broth is subtle and clean—not your usual sweet or tangy vibe—but add their house-made kelp vinegar and it hits different ✨
Plus, we tried Goldong Naengmyeon, a dry version with sesame oil and soy sauce… and honestly, I liked it even more

They also serve K-BBQ since it’s owned by Yellow Cow
Set A includes: brisket, boneless short rib (my fave), ribeye, and marinated short ribs—all melt-in-your-mouth good. Don’t skip wrapping your meat in Myungi Namul (game-changer)

🅿️ $3 valet in the back of the building!
